Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections

Class DynamicList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.DynamicList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the list items
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sizeable, Textable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.Deque<T>, java.util.List<T>, java.util.Queue<T>
    public class DynamicList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.List<T>, java.util.Deque<T>, java.util.Queue<T>, Sizeable, Textable

    Implementation of List with a self-correcting iterator which allows removing of items while in a for loop on the list. It is implemented as a linked list with a clever iterator that skips removed items while looping. Use this class when dealing with highly dynamic lists (where there are many insertions and deletions in the list).

    [NB:This was formerly known as AotList. Code modified from au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.AotList by Shayne Flint. Removed Query, and dependency from AotCollection and AotIterable.]

    Given the new facilities provided in java 8 lists, this class may be obsolete. For example, to remove items from a list can be done with instructions such as list.sublist(from,to).clear().

    Author:
    Shayne Flint - loooong ago.
    refactored by Jacques Gignoux - 30 Nov. 2018
